-- Rosneft Hires TNK-BP’s Ukraine Chief Casimiro, Vedomosti Says
-- B y   S t e p h e n   B i e r m a n
-- 2012-06-05T05:01:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-05/rosneft-hires-tnk-bp-s-ukraine-chief-casimiro-vedomosti-says.html
OAO Rosneft,  Russia ’s largest oil
company, hired Didier Casimiro from smaller competitor TNK-BP,
Vedomosti reported today, citing unidentified people familiar
the matter.  Casimiro, who ran TNK-BP’s Ukraine operations, was named
vice president of state-run Rosneft, the Moscow-based newspaper
said. Casimiro formerly worked for BP, which owns half of TNK-
BP, in  Belgium ,  Germany , the Netherlands and the U.K., Vedomosti
said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephen Bierman in Moscow at 
 sbierman1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
